{"key":"post-8568347","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8568347</id>\n<content>You don't case the bottom, and microwaves are horrible for mycology unless it's brand new.&amp;nbsp; You also don't sterilize casing mix because it's much more susceptible to contamination if sterilized.&amp;nbsp; That's why we pasteurize casing and substrate mixes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There's actually little to be gained by casing pf cakes.&amp;nbsp; They're already 2/3 vermiculite.&amp;nbsp; They make nice spawn to bulk substrates, or fruited as cakes.&amp;nbsp; You'll rarely get more total product from cased cakes as from using the dunk and roll tek and fruiting them for a few flushes as cakes.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8568533</next>\n<prev>8568239</prev>\n<first>8567931</first>\n<last>8568533</last>\n<when>1214529726</when>\n<utime>06/27/08 04:22 AM</utime>\n</post>"}